 {"id":"frankenpandas-hxob","title":"fd90.16: schema-qualified DROP TABLE in write_sql Replace branch","description":"fd90 sub-bead: schema-qualified DROP TABLE in write_sql's SqlIfExists::Replace branch. Currently the Replace path uses 'DROP TABLE IF EXISTS quote_sql_ident(table)' which (a) bypasses the conn.quote_identifier dispatch (so MySQL backticks etc. don't take effect) and (b) doesn't schema-qualify even when SqlWriteOptions.schema is Some on a multi-schema backend. fd90.15 already routes CREATE/INSERT through schema; this slice plugs the same gap on DROP. Add private helper sql_drop_table_query_in_schema(conn, table, schema) and use it from the Replace branch. 3 tests: bare DROP on stub, qualified DROP on multi-schema stub, SQLite silent-ignore round-trip via write_sql Replace + schema=Some.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:34:44.531937258Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T19:48:18.579664666Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T19:48:18.577113434Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fd90","review","schema","sql"]}
+{"id":"frankenpandas-hyyqx","title":"fd90.141: 5 concat_*_with_* variants used in README but not in prelude","description":"fd90.74-140 README audit. Concat: Full Options section (README lines 1215-1227) uses four concat variants:
  concat_dataframes_with_axis(&[&df1, &df2], 1)?;
  concat_dataframes_with_axis_join(&[&df1, &df2], 1, ConcatJoin::Inner)?;
  concat_dataframes_with_axis_join(&[&df1, &df2], 0, ConcatJoin::Inner)?;
  concat_dataframes_with_keys(&[&df1, &df2], &['train', 'test'])?;
  concat_dataframes_with_ignore_index(&[&df1, &df2])?;

But the prelude (crates/frankenpandas/src/lib.rs:228-231) only exposes the base concat_dataframes and concat_series — none of the _with_* variants are reachable from 'use frankenpandas::prelude::*'.

Verified: the variants are pub-used at the top level (lib.rs:43-47) so 'use frankenpandas::concat_dataframes_with_axis' works, but the documented prelude doesn't include them. Same gap pattern as fd90.121, fd90.125, fd90.126, fd90.127, fd90.128 — README documented surface needed prelude expansion.

A user copy-pasting the Concat: Full Options example from prelude::* would hit five 'cannot find function' errors.

Fix: add the 5 concat variants to the prelude:
  concat_dataframes_with_axis
  concat_dataframes_with_axis_join
  concat_dataframes_with_keys
  concat_dataframes_with_ignore_index
  concat_series_with_ignore_index

All already pub-used at top level. Verify with cargo build + cargo test -p frankenpandas --lib.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T13:26:47.059213187Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T13:28:25.286351659Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T13:28:25.283569597Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenpandas-i0ml","title":"fd90.19: SqlWriteOptions::method for multi-row INSERT batching","description":"Add SqlWriteOptions::method = SqlInsertMethod::{Single, Multi} matching pandas pd.to_sql(method='multi'). Single (default) emits one INSERT per row (current behavior). Multi batches rows into a single multi-row INSERT statement, chunked by conn.max_param_count() when set. Tests cover Single default, Multi chunking at param-count boundary, NaT/Null preservation, and fallback when max_param_count returns None.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:13:46.672143729Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:19:48.152994933Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:19:48.150361612Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fd90","review","sql"]}
